txt.en: Find the Elf at the Beorning watchpost

'An Elf passed through earlier, looking for dwarf ruins. She seemed lost and confused. I sent her to the Beornings at the edge of the Gladden Fields. They can deal with her; I have no time for such things. If you feel so inclined, you may wish to make sure she arrived safely.'

An Elf stands before you, attempting to get information out of the Beornings stationed here. She is polite, but they do not seem to be telling her what she needs to know. She notices your presence, and turns to you.\n\n'Hello, traveller, I am seeking information. May I ask you some questions?'
The Woodfolk of Laerlad tell you an Elf passed through looking for dwarf ruins, and was sent to the Beorning watchpost. Perhaps you should try and find this Elf.
This must be the Elf of whom Odahild spoke

An Elf was sent to the Beorning Watchpost in Gladden Fields by the Woodfolk in Laerlad.\n\nYou should see if this Elf made it to the watchpost.
